s and completed the four-year Education for Ministry course."},{"number":2,"category":"character","header":"Polymath with two-dozen mastered interests","body":"Bill's obituary listed his areas of personal expertise: religion, geography, physics, philosophy, history, sailing, scuba diving, underwater photography, amateur flying, classical and jazz music, theater, baseball, crossword puzzles, computer programming, sewing, toilet repair, genealogy, travel, and wine. He was 'a shameless braggart about his children.' His Yale engineering degree and UVA law degree were taken 'in deference' to his engineer father and lawyer mother."},{"number":3,"category":"family","header":"Outlived his son Frank Winter Hardie","body":"Bill's son Frank Winter Hardie (HD5039) died of neuroendocrine cancer at 28 in December 2007 — twelve years before Bill himself. He was survived by his other three children (Tuck, Ted, Rebecca) and four grandsons (Gabriel, Charles, Frank Tait, Jasper). Bill's wife Alix Winter survived him."}],"slug":"william-hardie-jr-1938"},"HD5038":{"id":"HD5038","has_descendants_documented":false,"classification":{"include_in_path_calculation":true,"descent_from_thomas_hooker":true,"descent_from_john_talcott":false,"is_thomas_descendant":true,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"generation_from_thomas":11,"is_easter_egg":false},"parents":{"father_id":"HD5035","mother_id":"X02872"},"tags":["died_in_infancy"],"sources":[],"marriages":[],"gender":"male","number_of_marriages":0,"notable":{"is_notable":false,"notable_category":[]},"birth":{"year":1943},"death":{"year":1943},"cross_connections":[],"bio":{"display_name":"Edson Hendrick Hardie","first_name":"Edson","last_name":"Hardie","middle_name":"Hendrick","married_names":[]},"residence":{},"baptism":{},"research_tags":[],"research_sources":[],"documents":[],"naming_inspiration":[],"institutions":[],"landmarks":[],"artworks":[],"quotes":[],"military_service":[],"slug":"edson-hardie-1943"}},"burialCemetery":null,"institutionsById":